							<div id="help_02_01" class="collapse show" aria-labelledby="help_h_02_01" data-parent="#accordionExample2">
							  <div class="card-body ">
								<p>To help you achieve your financial goals and trading objectives, we provide funding and liquidity support for your margin product trading activities. When you hold an overnight position in a margin product (such as a single stock CFD), you will need to pay a financing rate.
								</p><p>
								Your financing rate consists of two parts: 1) AFTT buy/sell financing rate and 2) the rate markup/markdown for the commercial product.
								</p><p>
								Financing rates are set as follows:<br>
									Buy = AFTT buy financing rate - Rate markdown for the commercial product
								<br>Sell = AFTT sell financing rate + Rate markup for the commercial product
								</p><p>
								AFTT Buy/Sell Financing Rates
								<br>The AFTT buy/sell financing rate refers to our pricing for financing, i.e., the charge for floating interest. When setting the AFTT buy/sell financing rate, we use Alternative Reference Rates (ARR) as input. If a currency does not have a designated Alternative Reference Rate, a money market rate, policy rate, or other relevant financial benchmark is used instead.
								<br>The minimum AFTT buy/sell financing rate is zero, meaning interest cannot be negative.
								</p><p>
								When buying a single stock CFD in HKD, we will convert the funding base to HKD to finance the purchase activity for that stock. Conversely, when selling a single stock CFD in ZAR, we will convert the proceeds from the sold stock into our funding base currency. These operations require active trading of different financial products in the interbank market to manage the liquidity flows generated by your trading activities.
								</p><p>
								Alternative Reference Rates are developed by working groups, which include domestic and international industry associations, market participants, and central banks. They are publicly available benchmark rates, recognized by National Competent Authorities (NCA), market participants, and domestic and international financial industry associations. For more information on the relevant financial benchmarks listed below, please consult the financial benchmark administrator, central banks, or reserve banks.
								</p><p>
								The AFTT buy/sell financing rate is proprietary to AFTT and is governed by the General Business Terms. One clause relates to cost pass-through associated with external factors, such as changes in domestic and/or international monetary or credit policies affecting overall interest levels, or changes in the cost structure of liquidity providers and brokers.
								</p><p>
								For reference, please see the applicable benchmark rates listed below.
								Rate Markup/Markdown for the Commercial Product
								</p><p>
								For more information on our general pricing, please visit the pricing overview page.
								</p><p>
								Interest Calculation and Settlement
								<br>
								We calculate your interest daily and settle it within seven business days of the end of each calendar month.</p>
							  </div>
